Tensions are high in Alexandria, in Johannesburg, as protesting residents clash with police. On Tuesday, police fired rubber bullets at people attempting to loot a number of shops in the area. Popular retail outlets, like the Pan Africa Shopping Centre, have completely shut down. Protesting residents took to the streets earlier to call on foreigners to leave, blaming them for drug dealing in the area. WATCH | 'Where is he?' Maimane calls on Ramaphosa to speak out Democratic Alliance Leader Mmusi Maimane called on President Cyril Ramaphosa to come out of hiding on Tuesday. His comments follow violent protests and looting in Gauteng and the deaths of UCT student Uyinene Mrwetyana and Leighandre Jegels. Watch. In neighbouring areas, there was also unrest. In Jeppestown and Malvern, residents looted shops, damaged property and torched cars on Monday. GET THE NEWS at your fingertips and download the News24 app for Android here now. Get it for your iPhone here. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter 